{"TopicId":170495,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Associating mods with saves?","CreatedByName":"Wcmille","CreatedById":151345,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-05T00:39:12Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Wcmille","CreatedById":151345,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-05T00:39:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat\u0027s the best way to associate certain mods with certain saves, so that when I use one save game, I get a certain set of mods, but when I use a different savegame, other mods are used?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E can handle the heavy lifting, but I\u0027d still need to reconfigure before launching KSP, right?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there something more streamlined?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-05T00:56:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think you\u0027ll be better off just running multiple full installs if you want to run different mods with different saves.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jas0n","CreatedById":57441,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-05T02:45:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr something I\u0027ve heard people do is having multiple Gamedata\u00A0folders and naming the ones you\u0027re not using something like GameData.stock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-05T02:48:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223285899\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221517798750\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257441\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jas0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Jas0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr something I\u0027ve heard people do is having multiple Gamedata\u00A0folders and naming the ones you\u0027re not using something like GameData.stock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s what I do.\u00A0 But I don\u0027t switch often.\u00A0 If you\u0027ve got the room and are playing different sets and switching frequently, multiple installs might be better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022MultiGameData.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022286\u0022 src=\u0022http://u.cubeupload.com/Geonovast/MultiGameData.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jas0n","CreatedById":57441,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-05T15:18:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223285901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221517798921\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179753\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geonovast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Geonovast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s what I do.\u00A0 But I don\u0027t switch often.\u00A0 If you\u0027ve got the room and are playing different sets and switching frequently, multiple installs might be better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://u.cubeupload.com/Geonovast/MultiGameData.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022MultiGameData.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022286\u0022 src=\u0022http://u.cubeupload.com/Geonovast/MultiGameData.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust out of curiosity, how does \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E work with such a setup? or do you have to install mods manually?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-05T15:23:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223286157\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022170495\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221517843888\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257441\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jas0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Jas0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust out of curiosity, how does \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E work with such a setup? or do you have to install mods manually?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 Tried once, but it didn\u0027t want to play well with WINE, and it\u0027s so easy to install mods manually that I didn\u0027t want to spend more than 2 seconds messing with it.\u00A0 But I would presume that it would work with whatever GameData folder you have active, i.e. just called \u0022GameData\u0022.\u00A0 Unless it keeps a log itself and doesn\u0027t scan the folder to see what you have installed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}